<!-- ko allowbindings: false -->
<!-- This file is automatically loaded into OctoPrint as a generic template, at the base of the web UI. -->
<div id="SimplyPrintWelcome" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Ã—</button>
        <h3 class="modal-title">
            <img alt="SimplyPrint logo (all rights reserved)" src="plugin/SimplyPrint/static/img/sp_logo.png">
            <span>Welcome to SimplyPrint!</span>
        </h3>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
        <div>
            <p id="spbiglcd"
               data-bind="css: {'dot-flashing': !settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.SimplyPrint.temp_short_setup_id().length}, visible: !settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.SimplyPrint.is_set_up()">
                <span data-bind="text: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.SimplyPrint.temp_short_setup_id"></span>
                <button class="btn light"><i class="fas fa-clipboard"></i></button>
            </p>
            <div class="alert alert-success alert-block"
                 data-bind="visible: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.SimplyPrint.is_set_up">
                <strong>Success!</strong> SimplyPrint is set up, you can now close this dialog.
            </div>

            <div class="text-center">
                <p style="font-size:20px;"><b>Return to the SimplyPrint setup</b>, and use this setup code if your
                    Raspberry Pi isn't automatically detected.</p>
                <hr>
                <h3>Not signed up to SimplyPrint yet?</h3>
                <p>Our mission is to make 3D printing simple and accessible for everyone.</p>
                <ul class="text-left">
                    <li>Print online - anywhere, on any device</li>
                    <li>Online in-browser slicer</li>
                    <li>Store your 3D files online</li>
                    <li>Web panel, iOS and Android app</li>
                    <li><i>and much, much, more...</i></li>
                </ul>
                <a href="https://simplyprint.io/signup?utm_source=octoprint" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary"
                   style="margin-top:10px;">
                    <i class="fas fa-sign-in-alt"></i> Sign up for free - it only takes 5 minutes
                </a>
                <p class="spwelcome-text-muted">
                    * free forever, no credit card required for our Free plan
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center" data-bind="visible: !settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.SimplyPrint.from_image()">
                <hr>
                <h4>What does SimplyPrint change / control in OctoPrint?</h4>
                <p>
                    There are a few OctoPrint-features which SimplyPrint takes control of - but don't worry, nothing is
                    gone, and the features SimplyPrint controls is changed through the SimplyPrint panel instead.
                </p>
                <ul class="text-left">
                    <li>
                        <b>Printer profile:</b>
                        <span class="help-inline">
                            Your old printer profile is saved, but an automatic one has been created and set to default by us, with all the correct settings <i>(non-stock settings like bounding box and heated chamber is not set)</i>
                        </span>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>GCODE scripts:</b>
                        <span class="help-inline">
                            The GCODE scripts for; <i>after cancel, after pause, before resume</i> is being controlled by the SimplyPrint GCODE profile manager instead.
                            If you have your own GCODE scritps set in the OctoPrint settings, they have been syncronized to SimplyPrint - nothing is lost :)
                        </span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
        <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
    </div>
</div>
